172. tumultuas = tumultuaris. Such a treatment of de- ponent verbs is a very characteristic feature of early Latin. Hence, in Cic. Att. iv. 16. 6, sortita = sorte ducta is quite right if the word be regarded as forming a part of the Setum, and therefore belonging to archaic language. A very long list of such verbs might be constructed from the early dramatists.
